# SMART Exchange Design System — Cursor Rules

> This document defines the visual language for the SMART Exchange platform.
> All styles MUST be implemented using pure Tailwind CSS utility classes — no custom CSS, no inline styles, no `<style>` blocks.

---

## General Principles

- **Pure Tailwind only.** Every visual style must be expressed as Tailwind utility classes. No custom CSS files (except the Tailwind base imports in `global.css`), no `<style>` tags, no inline `style=""` attributes. If a value isn't available in the default Tailwind config, use arbitrary value syntax (e.g. `bg-[#1E326F]`, `w-[325px]`).
- **Mobile-first responsive design.** Start with the smallest screen, layer up with `sm:` (640px) and `lg:` (1024px) breakpoints.
- **Inter is the primary typeface.** Applied via `font-['Inter']`. Weights used: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700. Secondary font: Meow Script (signature display only).
- **Minimal, clean aesthetic.** White/light gray backgrounds, subtle borders, restrained shadows, generous whitespace.
- **Accessibility.** All interactive elements need `focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-blue-600`. Use `sr-only` for screen-reader text. Proper `aria-label` on icon-only buttons.

